.TH GIT-NEW 1 "2026-07-23" "gitplus" "gitplus Manual"
.SH NAME
git-new \- create a branch and switch to it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git new
.I NAME
.br
.B git new
[\fB\-b\fR|\fB\-\-base\fR \fIBASE\fR]
.I NAME
.br
.B git new
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A thin wrapper around
.BR "git switch \-c" :
create branch
.I NAME
and switch to it, from the current branch by default, or from
.I BASE
if
.B \-b
is given.
.PP
Its real point is Tab-completion, not the wrapping: with the gitplus zsh
completions enabled,
.B "git new"
cycles through short words already used in this repository's existing branch
names (via
.BR _multi_parts ),
so composing a short name takes a few Tab presses instead of typing a
sentence \(em and it works no matter what is driving the terminal (an agent, a
script, you by hand), since the completion fires on the shell command itself,
not on anything choosing to cooperate. See the
.I README
for enabling the completions.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-base " " \fIBASE\fR
Branch from
.I BASE
instead of the current branch.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git new fix-md-crash
Create and switch to
.IR fix-md-crash ,
branching from the current branch.
.TP
.B git new \-b main hotfix-timeout
Create and switch to
.IR hotfix-timeout ,
branching from
.IR main .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-switch (1)
